---
import BaseLayout from "@layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import CtaButton from "@components/CtaButton.astro";
import PageHero from "@components/PageHero.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Home Every Weekend CDL-A Jobs | MNS1 Express" description="Choose 1, 2, or 3 weeks out — home on your designated Saturday for a full 34-hour reset.">
  <PageHero
    eyebrow="Home Time"
    title="Home When We Say You'll Be Home"
    accent="You'll Be Home"
    lead="Every carrier promises home time. We actually deliver it. Choose 1, 2, or 3 weeks out — home on your designated Saturday for a full 34-hour reset."
  >
    <div class="hero-actions">
      <CtaButton />
    </div>
  </PageHero>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="wrap section-heading">
      <p class="eyebrow">Flexible Schedules</p>
      <h2>Pick Your Rhythm</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="wrap grid grid--cards">
      <article class="card"><h2>1 Week Out</h2><p>Out Monday through Friday, home every weekend. Best for drivers close to Chicagoland who want maximum home time.</p><p>Most popular schedule</p></article>
      <article class="card"><h2>2 Weeks Out</h2><p>Two weeks on the road, then home for your 34-hour reset. A solid balance of miles and home time.</p><p>Maximum earning potential</p></article>
      <article class="card"><h2>3 Weeks Out</h2><p>Three weeks out, then home for an extended reset. Maximum miles for drivers who want to stack paychecks.</p></article>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="section section--panel">
    <div class="wrap split">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">How It Works</p>
        <h2>No Guessing Games</h2>
        <p>You pick your schedule at orientation. Dispatch builds your loads around your home date — not the other way around. Your designated Saturday is your designated Saturday. Period.</p>
      </div>
      <aside class="panel">
        <ul class="check-list">
          <li>Choose Your Schedule: 1, 2, or 3 weeks out. You pick at orientation.</li>
          <li>Designated Saturday: Home on your day for a full 34-hour reset.</li>
          <li>Consistent Pattern: Same rhythm every cycle. Plan your life around it.</li>
        </ul>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="wrap grid grid--cards">
      <article class="card"><p class="eyebrow">From Real Drivers</p><h2>Don't Take Our Word for It</h2><p>"I get home every Friday. When they say you'll be home, you're home. No excuses, no "maybe next week." It's real."</p><p>Sam A. MNS1 Driver</p></article>
      <article class="card"><p>"They do get you home every weekend. After two carriers that lied about home time, MNS1 actually delivers."</p><p>Jon H. MNS1 Driver</p></article>
      <article class="card"><p class="eyebrow">The Elephant in the Room</p><h2>"Every Carrier Says That"</h2><p>You're right — they do. And most of them are lying. You've probably been burned before. "Home every weekend" turns into "most weekends" which turns into "when we can."</p><p>At MNS1, the owner is in the building and still in the trenches with the team. That day-to-day accountability is why the home time promise sticks.</p><p>Five independent Google reviews confirm: the home time is real. Don't take our word for it — read them.</p></article>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="section section--panel">
    <div class="wrap panel">
      <h2>Ready to Get Home?</h2>
      <p>CDL-A, 24+ months experience. Apply in 4 mins and pick your home time schedule at orientation.</p>
      <p><a class="text-link" href="tel:6302463280">630-246-3280</a></p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
